<TITLE> Laila now a severe cyclonic storm </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)The cyclonic storm Laila over the west-central and adjoining southwest Bay of Bengal has moved slightly north-northwestwards and intensified into a severe cyclonic storm. The Meteorological Department said in special bulletin late on Wednesday. At 9pm, the storm was centred about 1380 km southwest of Chittagong port, 1335 km southwest of Cox's Bazaar port and 1215 km southwest of Mongla port. It is likely to move in a northerly direction and may cross northeast Andhra Pradesh coast of India near Visakhapatnam by Thursday morning Maximum sustained wind speed within 64 kms of the storm centre is about 89 kph rising to 117 kph in gusts or squalls. Sea will remain high. The Met Office advised the maritime ports to hoist 'distant warning signal number two.' Under the influence of severe cyclonic storm, deep convection is taking place over north Bay and adjoining coastal areas of Bangladesh. Squally weather is likely over north Bay, which will remain rough, and the coastal areas All fishing boats and trawlers over north Bay and deep sea have been advised to remain in shelter until further notice
